00:01:09.860 --> 00:01:13.460
&gt;&gt; Theresa Mims Davis: Donnie
Simpson began his career at the age

00:01:13.460 --> 00:01:18.730
of 15 at the urban contemporary
radio station, WJLB, in Detroit,

00:01:18.730 --> 00:01:22.580
Michigan, where he
remained for eight years.

00:01:22.580 --> 00:01:32.220 position:56%
In 1977, he relocated to Washington,
D.C. In 1983, Simpson was recruited

00:01:32.220 --> 00:01:34.800
by Bob Johnson, Founder of BET,

00:01:34.800 --> 00:01:41.190
to host the network's primetime
music video show, Video Soul.

00:01:41.190 --> 00:01:46.340
Simpson remained with the show
until its cancellation in 1997.

00:01:46.340 --> 00:01:51.590
He hosted the Donnie Simpson
Morning Show in Washington, D.C.,

00:01:51.590 --> 00:01:58.850
on radio station WPGC-FM from
March 1993 to January 2010.

00:01:58.850 --> 00:02:07.000 position:56%
Currently he hosts the Donnie
Simpson Show in D.C. on Majic 102.3.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:13.280
Simpson is the first urban
formal radio personality

00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:18.350
to have an annual salary of
over one million without,

00:02:18.350 --> 00:02:20.030
without being syndicated.

00:02:20.030 --> 00:02:22.040
[ Applause ]

00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:27.850
He was Billboard's 1998 Air
Personality of the Year.

00:02:27.850 --> 00:02:32.510
Ladies and gentlemen, I
present to you Donnie Simpson.

00:02:32.510 --> 00:02:40.040
[ Applause ]

00:02:40.040 --> 00:02:41.340
&gt;&gt; Donnie Simpson: Wow!

00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:43.610
Thank you!

00:02:43.610 --> 00:02:45.290
Thank you!

00:02:45.290 --> 00:02:47.030
Oh, my goodness.

00:02:47.030 --> 00:02:49.040
[ Laughter ]

00:02:49.040 --> 00:02:50.870
That million dollar number has
been out there for so long.

00:02:50.870 --> 00:02:52.170
It's so funny to me.

00:02:52.170 --> 00:02:55.280
I just laugh every time I hear it
because it's just, I don't know,

00:02:55.280 --> 00:02:57.080
I mean, it, it, what it are?

00:02:57.080 --> 00:03:01.050
You know? It, it is an honor,
but that's not why we do it.

00:03:01.050 --> 00:03:03.080
[ Laughter ]

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:04.790
But it's nice that
they pay you for it.

00:03:04.790 --> 00:03:07.780
As a matter of fact, I was
just telling the guys Thursday,

00:03:07.780 --> 00:03:10.010
during Thursday and
Friday show, I said,

00:03:10.010 --> 00:03:11.320
I even said it on the air I think.

00:03:11.320 --> 00:03:14.610
I, it's just still amazing to
me that they pay me for this.

00:03:14.610 --> 00:03:17.100
You know, because I
have so much fun.

00:03:17.100 --> 00:03:19.360
You know, I just love what I do.

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:22.600
You know, we sit there, man, shoot,
especially Thursday and Friday.

00:03:22.600 --> 00:03:25.590
We got the TV on, we're
watching the Master's.

00:03:25.590 --> 00:03:30.540
We got Teddy Pendergrass
and Luther playing.

00:03:30.540 --> 00:03:32.930
You know, telling jokes
and having fun.

00:03:32.930 --> 00:03:34.230
It's like, wow!

00:03:34.230 --> 00:03:36.540
And you get a check at the
end of the day, you know,

00:03:36.540 --> 00:03:41.100 position:56%
and I've been blessed to get away
with that for all my life, you know.

00:03:41.100 --> 00:03:46.190
Since I was 15, I've worked four
hours a day, five days a week,

00:03:46.190 --> 00:03:48.550
no weekends, all the
fun I can stand.

00:03:48.550 --> 00:03:52.030
I mean, I, you know, it's
like God is so good to me.

00:03:52.030 --> 00:03:54.050
[ Applause and Laughter ]

00:03:54.050 --> 00:03:56.610
He is. I'm telling you.

00:03:56.610 --> 00:04:00.490
Oh, so, well she kind of told
you how it started, so you know,

00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:03.230
I guess I should give
you some background.

00:04:03.230 --> 00:04:05.110
I started, I, Detroit boy.

00:04:05.110 --> 00:04:06.770
Born and raised in Detroit.

00:04:06.770 --> 00:04:08.350
Home of Motown.

00:04:08.350 --> 00:04:13.260
And growing up in Motown was
such a special occasion for me.

00:04:13.260 --> 00:04:15.460
It was just, wow!

00:04:15.460 --> 00:04:19.450
You know, we used to watch
every Cadillac that went by,

00:04:19.450 --> 00:04:25.270
just hoping that you'd see
Diana Ross or Marvin Gaye or one

00:04:25.270 --> 00:04:27.600
of the Temptations or
one of their cousins.

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:30.280
That would have been just as cool!

00:04:30.280 --> 00:04:31.600
That's exciting too.

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:35.430
Barber, anybody, anybody
that knows them, you know.

00:04:35.430 --> 00:04:37.600
And so, wow!

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:40.510
I'm skipped way ahead here
because I want to say this.

00:04:40.510 --> 00:04:45.250
That it's just amazing to me
that all these years later

00:04:45.250 --> 00:04:47.560
that these people are
friends of mine.

00:04:47.560 --> 00:04:51.700
You know, that I just don't quite
understand how that all happened.

00:04:51.700 --> 00:04:54.750
You know, it's just,
well, here's a video

00:04:54.750 --> 00:04:58.250
that so many people have
mentioned that it's on YouTube.

00:04:58.250 --> 00:05:01.420
It's with me and Aretha
Franklin on Video Soul,

00:05:01.420 --> 00:05:04.660
