the conversation started,

00:05:04.660 --> 00:05:07.040
but somehow it went
to Curtis Mayfield,

00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:13.000 position:56%
and we were doing a two-hour special
at Aretha's house, and so she start,

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.370
I'm sitting there with her at her
piano, and she just starts singing.

00:05:17.370 --> 00:05:20.500
Someone mentioned my favorite song
is The Makings of You, and she,

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:26.080
add a little sugar, honeysuckle
and, and I just started crying.

00:05:26.080 --> 00:05:31.360
I just started crying because there
was so much in that moment for me.

00:05:31.360 --> 00:05:34.400
You know, it was like
how did I get here?

00:05:34.400 --> 00:05:35.960
How, how did this happen?

00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:40.680
You sitting on the
queen's throne, one on one,

00:05:40.680 --> 00:05:42.730
greatest voice I've
ever heard in my life,

00:05:42.730 --> 00:05:45.660
singing to me, one
on one, in my ear.

00:05:45.660 --> 00:05:47.330
How did this, how did this happen?

00:05:47.330 --> 00:05:49.040
I'm not worthy, you know.

00:05:49.040 --> 00:05:52.970
Surely they're going to put me
out of here in a minute, you know.

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:57.490
But it's just, but you know what,
I guess God puts you exactly

00:05:57.490 --> 00:06:01.860
where he wants you to be, and so,
you know, I'm grateful for it.

00:06:01.860 --> 00:06:05.360
I, I still don't quite understand
how it has all happened, you know,

00:06:05.360 --> 00:06:08.560
for this little boy from Detroit
who admired these people so to grow

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:13.050
up to become, you know,
their friends and, you know,

00:06:13.050 --> 00:06:15.750
to, it's just, I don't know.

00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:17.220
It's overwhelming to me.

00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:18.520
It really is.

00:06:18.520 --> 00:06:21.770
To be here today, to see
this kind of welcome is,

00:06:21.770 --> 00:06:25.210
it's just, it's overwhelming.

00:06:25.210 --> 00:06:28.880
When I came back to radio after
five and half years' retirement,

00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:32.270
I mean all of the, the, the press
and the attention and stuff,

00:06:32.270 --> 00:06:33.820
it was just, I, I, I don't know.

00:06:33.820 --> 00:06:35.690
I guess I never get used to it.

00:06:35.690 --> 00:06:39.370 position:56%
It's just, when I retired, you know,

00:06:39.370 --> 00:06:43.010
and to see it on the front
page of the Washington Post.

00:06:43.010 --> 00:06:44.800
You know, above the fold.

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:46.100
I'll never forget.

00:06:46.100 --> 00:06:47.400
I got --

00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:49.080
[ Laughter ]

00:06:49.080 --> 00:06:50.380
Seriously.

00:06:50.380 --> 00:06:51.680
You know, I picked up
the paper that morning.

00:06:51.680 --> 00:06:52.980
I saw that.

00:06:52.980 --> 00:06:54.280
Immediately tears just
came to my eyes

00:06:54.280 --> 00:06:57.810
